Hello Vegas... It's always nice to come back for a visit. Weirdly it still always feels like coming home. For those that haven't known me a while, I grew up in the Las Vegas area (Boulder City specifically) before moving back to Canada for University. For a lot of people Vegas is nothing more then an adult playground. There's so much more in the area. For airspace reasons I intentionally went to the opposite end of the strip away from Harry Reid / Macaran Airport for airspace reasons... Which also happens to be the sketches part of town. Good times.

@venuslaowa was kind enough to send over one of their new 6mm Zero Distortion lenses for some testing. The lack of barrel distortion with this width is completely wild. I'll be out there battling the -30 temps and snow the next few days to put the lens to work. Venus Laowa has made some unique and incredibly powerful lenses recently, including one of my all-time favorites, the 24mm Macro Probe. This 6mm looks to be another solid optical option.

Exposure... Some low-light, long exposure photos from last night's mission. These were captured through the new @venuslaowa 6mm Zero Distortion lens on my Inspire 2. The light streak effect is created through the drone and the long shutter duration, holding framing for the first several seconds of the shot, then panning through the Yaw stick for half of the shot. When the conditions allow for long exposure images the results can be pretty wild. There's a few little tricks to get the drone as stable as possible with wind. The first two were captured as 8 second shutter durations wide open. The third image was 12 second exposure, at F4.0. The 6mm lens is proving to be quite powerful!

@venuslaowa #venusopticslaowa #6mm #6mmZeroDistortion @nanukcases #nanuk @djipro #dji #inspire2 #inspire #drone #djifpv @trentuniversity #TrentU

Dual Season... I've been working on a new round of multi-season composite shots. It takes a while, literally a year, to capture the same image under multiple seasons, but the results can be worth it. This image was one of the original tests in the series a few years ago, back when I was working out how to make the composites logistically work. I never shared this one. The biggest factor is the placement of the sun and shadows, as the lighting source varies widely through the seasons, putting shadows at different angles. You can compensate by capturing the images at differing times of day. Lots of note-taking to make these happen. More from the new series soon. @nanukcases 

#DualSeason #drone #aerials #dji @djipro @djiglobal #inspire #inspire2 #nanukcases @nanukcases @thekawarthas #DiscoverON @ontariotravel

Testing... Testing, Testing... The brand new @djiglobal M350 RTK at sunset as we calibrate and test. We were extremely fortunate to take delivery of an early Matrice 350 RTK hull, lining up the equipment for the top-secret drone project that my company has stealthily worked on the last two years. We received full federal approval for the system last week in Ottawa, which was a huge step. At this time I can't share too much more about the system, but we can show this absolute monster of a drone. The pieces are all coming together for the project, and we'll be able to share more soon, I promise!  Thank you to @nick.strode for manning the second drone angle. @djipro

@nanukcases #nanuk #Matrice #M350RTK #Matrice350 #dji #djienterprise #aviation #Mavic3pro #Mavic3 #sunset #drone

In some of the recent stories and posts I had a few people ask about the size/scale of the M350. It's definitely not compact, but with this size we can increase the payload. Currently using quite powerful optics with the system. Swipe over to see some zoom samples from the testing. The first clip was at a height of 400ft in 25knot winds, and the marina across the lake is about 1.5km from the drone. The system is massively promising, and I can't wait to be able to show everything the rest of what we've developed. Wait until you see the pickup truck we're building it into. #dronethings 📷@nick.strode

#Drone #dji #Matrice #Matrice350RTK #M350RTK #m350 #inspire #Mavic #nanuk @nanukcases #dronedevelopment

The "Project" ... I can finally talk about what it is that I've been working on for the last three years. Through a three-company partnership,  I was tasked with creating a specialized drone platform through my company, one that could operate within restricted and controlled airspace, at airports within the threshold of aircraft taking off an landing. Operstions at all times in all weather. The goal is to provide a mobile and flexible platform with an extremely powerful optic that can image and scan aircraft during the de-icing process. Prior to this technology, de-icing checks were done visually from within aircraft by pilots and cabin crew. This system completely revolutionizes the system, giving extremely accurate images in real-time to the pilot flight deck through the integrated software system running on pilot's ipads. With this system a pilot can see exactly how effective deicing was in real time, increasing safety and efficiency a hundred fold. To date there has never been a system like this, running the tether to a designated truck ground station and dock. We have full, complete blanket approval from Transport Canada to run the system at every airport in Canada, and we're working on permissions for the United States and Europe as well. This will be huge, and it has been a pleasure working with the team to get this across the finishline. My company will now be focusing on drone development, assembly and deployment for the system as we roll it out. Photos by @nick.strode who also operated as my second-in-command during development. Thank you.

#drone #aviation #YOW #dji @djiglobal #Matrice #Matrice350RTK #M350

social_posts.post_text:
Another week and we've wrapped up the main demonstration phase of the tethered drone deicing-scan system. This round at Ottawa International Airport was for a group of airline executives, millitary, Transport Canada and Nav Canada ATC representatives. It's always an incredibly hectic time-frame to line all of the logistics up for a large demonstration, but the system has been flawless. Now we move on to deployment of the drone system. I also need to thank the Ottawa Airport staff for working with us so closely, but most importantly a huge thank you to @nick.strode and @audreyember for assisting during this one.
